Step 1: Determine the average total assets.  
• Initial Total Assets = 13,000,000.00  
• End Total Assets = 14,214,117.02  
Average Total Assets = (13,000,000.00 + 14,214,117.02) / 2  
  = 27,214,117.02 / 2  
  ≈ 13,607,058.51  

Step 2: Get the Net Profit from the income statement which is 835,266.51.

Step 3: Calculate the Return on Assets (ROA) using the formula:  
  ROA = (Net Profit / Average Total Assets) × 100%  
  = (835,266.51 / 13,607,058.51) × 100%  
  ≈ 6.14%

Thus, the ROA is approximately 6.14%.
